X:1
T:Auld Lang Syne
C:Robert Burns (lyrics, 1788), trad. Scottish (melody)
S:Public domain (US) — both lyrics (1788) and melody pre-1929 by
S:over a century.
N:The single most-played pipe tune at New Year's. The original
N:soprano-voice setting in F major fits the chanter neatly when
N:transposed up a major 3rd into A mixolydian — the lowest note
N:becomes low A and the highest note sits on high A. NO RESTS —
N:phrase ends are held notes, not silences.
M:4/4
L:1/8
Q:1/4=80
K:Amix
H:Range: low A (A4) to high A (A5). All nine chanter notes used.
H:Arrangement: Heifer Zephyr / Tony Koop, 2026 (MIT, sheet-music repo).
H:Pipers commonly play this slowly at memorial services and
H:briskly at New Year. ♩ = 80 splits the difference; adjust to
H:taste. Doublings carry the rhythmic weight; in pipe-band
H:massed-band settings the snare drum carries it instead.
% --- 16-bar through-form, no internal repeat ---
{GdG}A2 |\
{GdG}A2 A2 A2 c2 | {GdG}c2 B2 A2 B2 | {GdG}c2 A2 A2 c2 | {GeG}e6 e2 |
{ge}e2 {gf}f2 e2 a2 | {gag}a2 a2 g2 f2 | {GdG}A2 B2 c2 B2 | {GBG}A6 A2 |
{GdG}A2 A2 A2 c2 | {GdG}c2 B2 A2 B2 | {GdG}c2 A2 A2 c2 | {GeG}e6 e2 |
{ge}e2 {gf}f2 e2 a2 | {gag}a2 a2 g2 f2 | {GdG}A2 B2 c2 B2 | {GBG}A8 |]
